<subSubSection pageId="632" pageNumber="633" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="632" pageNumber="633">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="632" pageNumber="633">This subspecies ranges from south-central New York (Ball 1959: 213) to southeastern Nebraska (Lancaster County, UASM), including southern Wisconsin (Rauterberg 1885: 17; Purrington et al. 2002: 201), south to southern Texas (Gonzales County, CMNH; Brazoria County, Robert L. Davidson pers. comm. 2008) and southern Florida (Peck and Thomas 1998: 21); also recorded from the Bahamas (Darlington 1953: 8).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
